WHY main METHOD IS STATIC (ğŸ”¥ INTERVIEW Q)
public static void main(String[] args)
ğŸ“Œ Best answer:
â€œJVM needs to call main without creating an object, so it must be static

REAL PROJECT CONTEXT (IMPRESSIVE)

Constants â†’ static final
Utility methods â†’ static
Configuration values â†’ static
ğŸ“Œ Smart line:
â€œStatic is commonly used for constants and utility methods.â€

1. static method cannot direclty access instance variables
static blong to class
instance variable belong to objects
At the time a static method runs, no object may exist

class Test {
  int x = 10;
  static void show() {
      System.out.println(x) ;// compile time error
  }
}

correct way:

Static method can access instance data only through an object
class Test {
    int x = 10;

    static void show() {
        Test obj = new Test();
        System.out.println(obj.x); // âœ… allowed
    }
}

